snippet: Intelligence gathered thus far is seen by American officials as inconclusive and claims of responsibility as less than credible.
abstract: United States officials have been excessively cautious in determining cause of crash of Russian charter jet in Sinai Peninsula, in large part because combination of factors has led to dearth of reliable information that would shed accurate light on event.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Matthew Rosenberg, Matt Apuzzo, Eric Schmitt, Michael S. Schmidt and David E. Sanger.

lead_paragraph: Intelligence gathered thus far is seen by American officials as inconclusive and claims of responsibility as less than credible.

headline.main: Spotty Intelligence Prompts U.S. Caution in Assessing Jet Crash in Egypt
headline.print_headline: Spotty Intelligence Prompts U.S. Caution in Assessing Cause of Jet Crash
